#Qingdao has a lot of well-preserved German and Japanese colonial architecture (1898-1922), but this cathedral was actually built by the German after the city returned to Chinese rule in the 1930s. #explorechinawithcvz

The Jiaozhou Bay region in northwest China was once a German colony from 1898 to 1914 and #Qingdao was developed as the capital of the region. Though the German colonial history only lasted for 15 years (it was later occupied by the Empire of Japan until 1922), many buildings were constructed, and quite a lot of them are still here today. #explorechinawithcvz

Before the 50s, much of Hong Kong was not yet urbanized except Hong Kong Island, the Kowloon Peninsula and part of the new Kowloon (Sham Shui Po). New towns were later created to relocate the overcrowded population. #KwunTong was the first 'new town'. A typical 'new town' created back then usually have both a residential and industrial area and an area defined as 'Town Centre', which you can still hear that in bus announcements.

Sri Lanka has a Portuguese, Dutch and British colonial history. Back in the early 16th century, the Portuguese found a walled city in #Colombo. Most of the remaining European-style buildings in Fort, the former fortified town, date back to the British colonial era (1802-1948). This city is full of history and I'm happy to see that old buildings are getting renovated. I'm sure I'll be back to explore this country someday! #exploresrilankawithcvz

What I love the most about traveling is that it gets me searching for what has shaped the things we see in a place today, and it's even better if I could learn it from locals. #osaka #explorejapanwithcvz

Remnant of the old #Osaka. Though the number of surviving old wooden houses in #Nakazakicho is not as large as Kyoto, which was spared from WWII bombing, it is still a really lovely area to stroll around in central Osaka. #explorejapanwithcvz

I'm quite impressed by the Korea Town in #Osaka. During the Japanese colonial era and Korean war, some Korean moved to Japan. The Korean community in Osaka, a boomtown in the early 20th century, is still very huge today, and you can find everything, from kimchi to K-Pop products, in #Tsuruhashi. #explorejapanwithcvz
Look for the old Osaka in the modern-looking #Kitahama area. #explorejapanwithcvz
Do you know back in the 1930s, #Osaka was the largest city in Japan? #explorejapanwithcvz
